cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

This paper deals with the problem of finding optimal feedback controllers for nonlinear dynamic systems using Bayesian optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. The paper also deals with control systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes a specific kernel design for the Gaussian process used in Bayesian optimization, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with simulations of uncertain linear and nonlinear systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
